### Is this a regression?

No

### Description

The current typing of the createNgModuleRef function is:
```
export declare function createNgModuleRef<T>(ngModule: Type<T>, parentInjector?: Injector): NgModuleRef<T>;
```
The problem with this is in cases when more lazy loaded modules should be processed with the same generic code, like:
```
export enum LazyModules {
	EDITOR = 'editor',
	PROFILE = 'profile'
}

export const lazyLoadedModules = {
	[LazyModules.EDITOR]: {
		loadChildren: async () => (await import('@pall/lazy-modules/editor')).LazyEditorModule
	},
	[LazyModules.PROFILE]: {
		loadChildren: async () => (await import('@pall/lazy-modules/profile')).LazyProfileModule
	}
};

lazyLoadedModules[lazyModule].loadChildren().then(module => {
	const moduleRef = createNgModuleRef(module, this._injector);
	...
}
```
because the createNgModuleRef typing is not able to process type variants and the following error is appearing:
```
The argument of type 'typeof LazyEditorModule | typeof LazyProfileModule' is not assignable to the parameter of type 'Type<LazyEditorModule>'.
  Type 'typeof LazyProfileModule' is not assignable to type 'Type<LazyEditorModule>'.
```

When this happens the less efficient code is necessary to use:
```
export const lazyLoadedModuleEditor = {
	loadChildren: async () => (await import('@pall/lazy-modules/editor')).LazyEditorModule
};

export const lazyLoadedModuleProfile = {
	loadChildren: async () => (await import('@pall/lazy-modules/profile')).LazyProfileModule
};

switch (lazyModule) {
	case LazyModules.EDITOR:
		lazyLoadedModuleEditor.loadChildren().then(module => {
			const moduleRef = createNgModuleRef(module, this._injector);
			...
		})
		break;
	case LazyModules.PROFILE:
		lazyLoadedModuleProfile.loadChildren().then(module => {
			const moduleRef = createNgModuleRef(module, this._injector);
			...
		})
		break;
```

The typing of the createNgModuleRef function should be instead:
```
export declare function createNgModuleRef(ngModule: Type<any>, parentInjector?: Injector): NgModuleRef<any>;
```
to allow a more universal code structure.

